&lt;p&gt;Hence, the&amp;nbsp;correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;294&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;In this question, three statements are given, followed by two conclusions numbered I and II. Assuming the statements to be true, even if they seem to be at variance with commonly known facts, decide which of the conclusions logically follows/follow from the statements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. Some lotuses are daisies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. No daisy is a rose.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;III. All thorns are roses.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. No thorn is a daisy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. Some roses are lotuses&lt;/p&gt;

