&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logic: In all other pairs &amp;rArr; (1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; number &amp;ndash; 4) &amp;divide; 2 = 2&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; number&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) 130 &amp;mdash; 63 &amp;rArr; (130 &amp;ndash; 4) &amp;divide; 2 = 126/2 = 63&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) 108 &amp;mdash; 52 &amp;rArr; (108 &amp;ndash; 4) &amp;divide; 2 = 104/2 = 52&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) 156 &amp;mdash; 76 &amp;rArr; (156 &amp;ndash; 4) &amp;divide; 2 = 152/2 = 76&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4) 94 &amp;mdash; 46 &amp;rArr; (94 &amp;ndash; 4) &amp;divide; 2 = 90/2 = 45&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
Hence, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;94 &amp;ndash; 46&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; is odd among given alternatives.

